GIF89a INERT FIXTURE — DO NOT SERVE FROM AN APPLICATION ORIGIN OR OPEN IN A BROWSER
Purpose: simulates a polyglot file that starts with a valid GIF magic byte sequence
and also contains an HTML/JS payload.
Threat: if this file is served from the application origin without X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
and a strict CSP, some browsers may execute it as HTML when navigated to directly.
The control is to serve uploads from a separate cookieless origin and set nosniff.

POLYGLOT PAYLOAD AREA (inert — magic bytes above make this pass naive GIF validation):
<html><body><script>alert('polyglot XSS: this file passed as a GIF but executed as HTML')</script></body></html>
